## Instructions

Generate a briefing with TWO sections:

### Section 1: Recap (2-3 sentences)
A brief "previously on..." recap that:
- Reminds the player where they left off
- Mentions their current objective or next action if available
- Uses a warm, encouraging tone — like a TV series recap
- ONLY mentions facts from the session notes above. Do NOT invent details not in the notes.
- If this is the first session, give a short welcome message instead.

### Section 2: Suggested next steps (2-3 bullet points)
Specific, actionable suggestions for what the player could do this session. Use your knowledge of the game's map, progression, and mechanics to give CONCRETE guidance:

WHAT MAKES A GOOD SUGGESTION:
- Reference specific areas or rooms the player has ALREADY visited where new abilities/items open previously blocked paths. Example: "With the double jump, go back to [area player mentioned] — there was a high ledge you couldn't reach that leads somewhere new."
- Name areas the player already knows. If they said they were in "City of Tears", reference specific parts of it or adjacent areas that are natural next steps in the game's progression.
- When the player obtains a new ability or item, tell them which previously visited areas now have newly accessible paths. Metroidvania-style games especially depend on this.
- Suggest a specific direction on the map: "head to the left side of [known area]" or "try going down from [known location]."
- Mix main progression with optional content: one bullet for advancing the main path, one for revisiting old areas with new abilities, one for exploration/side content.

WHAT MAKES A BAD SUGGESTION (avoid these):
- Generic advice like "practice your new ability" or "explore the surrounding area"
- Vague filler like "there seems to be more to discover nearby"
- Repeating what the player already told you without adding anything

SPOILER-FREE RULES (CRITICAL — these override everything above):
- NEVER reveal boss names, enemy names, or NPC names the player hasn't already mentioned
- NEVER reveal plot twists, story events, or narrative surprises
- NEVER name specific items, rewards, or upgrades the player hasn't mentioned
- You CAN name areas/zones/regions that are adjacent to where the player is — knowing a zone name is not a spoiler
- You CAN say "there's a path you couldn't reach before" — the existence of a blocked path is not a spoiler
- You CANNOT say what is at the end of that path (no boss names, no item reveals)

## Output format

Return the briefing as plain text with this structure:

[Recap paragraph]

What you could do this session:
- [suggestion 1]
- [suggestion 2]
- [suggestion 3 if relevant]

No JSON, no markdown headers, no code blocks.
